@startuml system-flow-with-cdn
title Live streaming system flow (with CDN for playback)

skinparam handwritten true
skinparam backgroundColor #1a1a1a
skinparam defaultFontColor #f5f5f5
skinparam arrowColor #e0e0e0
skinparam rectangleBackgroundColor #2d2d2d
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #888888
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #2d2d2d
skinparam databaseBorderColor #888888

skinparam noteBackgroundColor #2a2832
skinparam noteBorderColor #8b8680
skinparam noteFontColor #f0ebe3
skinparam noteFontSize 13

' --- Clients ---
rectangle "Client (Streamer)" as streamer #2d2d2d
note right of streamer
  using OBS
  H.264 compression
  **Example ingest URL**
  rtmp://your-platform.com/live/streamer_12345
end note

rectangle "Client (Web / iPhone / Android)" as viewers #2d2d2d
note right of viewers
  streaming options
  HLS (15s+ latency)
  LL-HLS (3-5s latency)
end note

' --- Edge & media (rectangle: avoids cloud keyword issues on some renderers) ---
rectangle "CDN\n(edge cache, segment delivery)" as cdn #3a3a4a

rectangle "Media Server (SRS)\n(origin for HLS / LL-HLS)" as srs #2d2d2d

rectangle "Transcode Module" as transcode #2d2d2d
note bottom of transcode
  create different quality outputs
  480, 720, 1080
end note

' --- Application tier ---
rectangle "API Gateway\n- routing\n- load balancer\n- middleware" as gateway #2d2d2d

rectangle "Backend Server\n(horizontal scaling + load balancing)" as backend #2d2d2d

database "DB\n(PostgreSQL / durable state)" as db #2d2d2d
note right of db
  Chat, gifts, wallet,
  DM, leaderboard, admin
end note

database "Cache (Redis)" as redis #2d2d2d
note top of redis
  distributed lock
end note

rectangle "Message queue\n(NATS / Redis Streams)" as mq #2d2d2d

rectangle "Worker\n(async media persistence)" as worker #2d2d2d
note bottom of worker
  Consumes jobs: finalize ingest record
  or transcode output, upload **VOD /
  replay** assets, write playback URLs.
end note

rectangle "Object storage\n(S3-compatible)" as obj #2d2d2d
note bottom of obj
  Durable **replay** manifests + segments
  (or MP4). Often fronted by CDN for VOD.
end note

' --- Ingest & transcode ---
streamer -down-> srs : **RTMP**
srs <-> transcode : transcode pipeline

' --- Signaling & app API ---
streamer <-> gateway : **WebSocket (chat)**\n**REST (API)**
viewers <-> gateway : **WebSocket (chat)**\n**REST (API)**
gateway <-> backend

' --- SRS callbacks & data ---
srs -down-> backend : **callback**\n(on_publish / on_unpublish,\non_record, etc.)
backend <-> db
backend <-> redis : **distributed lock**\ncache / sessions

' --- Async VOD / replay persistence (off request path) ---
backend ..> mq : **publish job**\n(record done, packaging)
mq ..> worker : **consume**
worker ..> srs : **read**\nrecorded files\n(shared volume / fetch)
worker -right-> obj : **upload**\nHLS / MP4 for replay
worker ..> db : **VOD metadata**\n(playback URL, status)

' --- Playback: origin -> CDN -> viewers (production pattern) ---
srs -right-> cdn : **LL-HLS / HLS**\n(origin pull or push)
cdn -down-> viewers : **LL-HLS / HLS**\n(low-latency segments)

note bottom of cdn
  **Live:** viewers hit CDN; origin is SRS.
  **Replay:** CDN (or signed URLs) may origin
  from **object storage** after worker upload.
end note

@enduml
